Boolean operation is one way to add geo, but there is a chance to create corrupted geo. A safer approach would be create the shape with edges and vertices and then snapping to the target geo, combine and merge vertices. If the shape is simple enough, we can extrude and build the shape directly. 

Here is an example, of referencing object. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Let's create a plane with enough subdivisions. Then, create a eight-side cylinder and start referencing it. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The shape is simple, so we use extrude and scale to build it directly. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Here comes the magic, with correct beveling, smooth operation can blend different shapes together though they are the same geo underneath.
